data.description: Welcome to the Red Brick Streets of Tyler’s Azalea  District! We're happy you're here! This 4 bedroom, 2.5 bath home has unlimited opportunities.  Built in 1924, this cottage style encompasses every bit of its historical charm. With updates along the way, it holds the delight of its original architecture and is withIn walking distance of a local coffee shop, bakery, pharmacy, & nail salon.   With easy access to Tyler’s thriving downtown, this home is conveniently located close to shopping, businesses, Christus and UT Tyler hospitals, TJC and Bergfeld park all while being quietly tucked away in a beautiful brick street neighborhood of Tyler, Texas.  This inviting property is perfectly planned to have a stand alone office space, mother in law suite, or private get away for guests while providing separated living space for your family.   Looking to add to your portfolio? This opportunity is currently income producing. The floor plan accesses a 3 bedroom/1.5 bath through the front door with a cloistered 1 bedroom/1 bath apartment from the back with each providing separate living, kitchen, & laundry.   In the highly sought after Azalea District, whether you're wanting a dreamy rental to add to your portfolio or an amazing home for your family, do not miss the chance to walk through and see if this historic home is the right fit for you!
